data.text: She is currently empowered by the souls of her ancestors.  So she's magic.  It's a 180 for her to suddenly be who she is in the movie who is completely different.  But that's never stopped comics before.  I just wonder how theyre gonna reconcile that difference if at all.

Where movie Shuri is a wise cracking teen with genius IQ chilling in a lab, comic Shuri is a grim character.  She's Black Panther cranked up to 11, his equal if not his better.  A stern Queen who believes in Wakanda's traditions.
